How do I join the data 001 piazza?
Go to join another class at the bottom of the drop down menu, click "Other" for the term (I think), and then type data 001. Should show up!

<md>At which part did it not work, like did it not show up? Did you make sure to type `DATA 001: Data Science Support` and not `DATA 101` (I made the same mistake since I was already here in EECS 101 haha)? And are you sure you selected `Other` as your term?</md>

Hi! I was able to get it :). The issue was because i was in FPF when I was a freshman piazza automatically tried to enroll me in berkeley extension classes, and because data 001 is not a berkeley extension class, I was having trouble enrolling: somehow I was able to switch it though. Thank you!
<md>Is Data 8 looking for AI/TA's?</md>
yea, AIs are compensated with 1-2 units.

<md>Yes. Workload associated and flexibility of units is decided on a course level though. 

To get the units in the summer you have to pay for summer units. Otherwise, you receive them for free the following Fall semester.</md>
<md>Can you get a unit for being an AI for the summer?</md>

<md>You are correct it does not seem to be released. I know at least for 61BL, it is a formality that is required by the department before we hire you, whereas the google form we put out is what we use to determine interviews. <md>Please make sure to fill it out when it is released!</md>
There does not seem to be an option to select "No" for "Did you fill out the official department application for GSIs?" on the 61BL app, should we just select yes because it hasn't been released yet?
<md>Yes.</md>
is it just me, or is the ASE app not out yet?
<md>You can select Other and enter an explanation (e.g. currently in class)</md>

There is now a "Currently taking" option on the form.

Ishaan you look so classy in your piazza profile pic. I also encourage you to apply to be on cs61a course staff if you are free this summer!
Zoe, I'm a fan of the Piazza profile picture

You do not need to enroll in any classes. If you are a first time TA, you need to take CS375, but you can push back getting those units until fall so you don't have to pay money to get units during the summer.
is cs 370 ok? or does it have to be cs 375
If you've already taken 370 you're fine, if you haven't then then you'll need to take 375 because 370 isn't taught in the summer
yup ^
thank you!
Do I need to enroll in Summer 2021 in order to get any course staff position?
Data 8 and 100 are on a separate hiring schedule. You can expect applications to be posted here (ie. EECS 101 Piazza) later
Data C100?
Feel free to mention that to the course staff you’re applying for
But how do I know I'm eligible to apply in the first place? I rather not go through everything to find out I don't meet one requirement.
<md>Requirements are here: https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/gsis/prospective/ugrad you can email the eecs staff about your specific situation. </md>

Ok, I see:

> Have previously taken the course, its equivalent or a more advanced course, with a grade of A- or better

<md>Time flies like an arrow. Fruit flies like a banana. </md>
Miss you Suraj :(
Time flies!
Check out the Berkelely academic guide, the instructors are listed up to date for the cs classes I believe
who are the summer instructors for each course?

An AI is an unpaid position compensated at 1 units/3 hrs (1 unit/6 hrs during the summer) while a tutor is a paid position compensated at roughly $19.60/hr. AIs usually assist in labs while tutors run small group sections.

Quick question! Is there a difference between an Academic Intern and a Tutor?
I'm currently taking 61A this semester, and just wanted to confirm. Thank you!
You can list it in "Please list any additional relevant courses.." instead, and indicate that it was PNP
For the 70 app, it asks for grades in other classes. What should you do if you took some of those classes pass no pass in Spring 2020 and you do not know the equivalent grade?
You can submit the Google form now, just make sure to also submit the official GSI application when it is released.
<md>For the cs70 position, it requires us to fill out the GSI application; however, the Berkeley website only has applications for the Spring and Fall term -- not Summer. What should we do? </md>
<md>As far as I know there aren't any rules against it. </md>
I tried this last summer and WOULD NOT recommend it.
Adding to that ^; neither did I receive a full-time offer nor did I do enough to get a high uGSI rating. :/
Is it possible to do a fulltime internship (40hrs/week) along with TAing?

61BL is basically a lab-based version of 61B (4 labs per week, 1 lecture per week, and no discussions), so the majority of the learning happens in lab sections with the students' TAs. And yeah, you can definitely be on staff for 61BL even if you've taken 61B (I did the same!)
This might be a stupid question, but what is CS61BL? If I have taken CS61B, can I apply the staff and/or AI for that?
Data science apps will (probably) be a separate post
Where could I find application for data 8 course staff? Will it be added here
^ same question. is there a priority deadline?

<md>There is a priority deadline for CS61BL of February 21st at 11:59pm pacific time. This will be added to the general post above. After, we will accept applications on a rolling basis until the deadline provided in the application.</md>
What is the due date for the AI/Tutor applications? Are the applications approved on a rolling basis? Thanks.

<md>Unfortunately, we have no control over when the department will release it. So long as you fill it out before you are hired, you should not encounter any issues. We can ping in this thread when we notice that it has been posted.</md>
When is the ASE application going to be released?
My fault for not getting it up earlier...
Bad human

You do not need to fill out the ASE form for AI positions, this is the form you should fill out instead!

upper division standing means you are a third year or a fourth year

>= 60, I believe

oh seems it has a different meaning in this context. Given how 60 upperdiv units is not done but most juniors/seniors you can probably safely assume it means overall.
aight cool cool thanks
Correct, overall

Yes

"The EECS Department has been informed that UC expects employees to conduct work within the United States. For Summer 2021, the campus is not authorized to hire applicants who did not previously hold an ASE appointment in the 2020-2021 academic year. The campus is able to make an exception which allows individuals who worked as an ASE during the 2020-2021 academic year and are not able to enter the U.S. due to travel restrictions or embassy closures to work from outside of the U.S."
